status: MARC21-007: Platform construction type of remote sensing device
Type of construction of the platform serving as the base for the remote-sensing device. "Platform" refers to any structure that serves as a base, not only flat surfaces.

definition (en): Base for the remote-sensing device was a balloon or similar lighter-than-air platform.
Base for the remote-sensing device was an dynamic lift aircraft designed for low altitude flight (below 29,500 ft. (8,962 m.)).
Base for the remote-sensing device was an dynamic lift aircraft designed for medium altitude flight (between 29,500 ft. (8,962 m.) and 49,000 ft. (14,810 m.)).
Base for the remote-sensing device was an dynamic lift aircraft designed for high altitude flight (above 49,000 ft. (14,810 m.)).
Base for the remote-sensing device was a manned spacecraft.
Base for the remote-sensing device was an unmanned spacecraft.
Base for the remote-sensing device was a land-based.
Base for the remote-sensing device was designed to remain on the surface of a body of water.
scope note (en): E.g., a ship or floating platform

definition (en): Base for the remote-sensing device was designed to be submerged beneath the surface of a body of water
scope note (en): E.g., a submersible vessel or platform

definition (en): Construction type of the platform from which the remote-sensing image was made is not known.

Platform construction type other than balloon, aircraft - low altitude, aircraft - medium altitude, aircraft - high altitude, manned spacecraft, unmanned spacecraft, land-based remote-sensing device, water surface-based remote-sensing device, submersible remote-sensing device.
